wiki.content: This track is as emotionally evocative as the name it bears. From Wikipedia: "Sehnsucht is one of those quasi-mystical terms in German for which there is no satisfactory corresponding term in another language...Literally translated, it means 'longing'". Sensucht was a recurring theme and point of exploration for CS Lewis. http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sehnsucht User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License and may also be available under the GNU FDL.

comments: Took me about 3 listens to realise how amazing this is <3
By far and away the best track on Berlinette.

when I heard this track for the first time back in 2004 I instanly loved it. And after all these years, and despite all great tracks that followed, it's still my favorite Ellen Allien track! simply awesome - love it!
Someway this track is just excellent. I won't be bored even after 100th replay.
This is my favorite track on this album!
Love the instrumental, but not "Pam Pam" vocals for me please.
Ellen, when you come to fameland, say HI in Hollywood!

this is for some reasons so emotionalizing for me, it is truly a thing of beauty
Ellen is Wunderbar!
